<br>
Shirf, the Armsman Teamleader resigned from Teamleader on 5/12 of this year (2003)..<br>
<br>
&quot;..I left the TL program in frustration over several points. The frustration wasn’t just in being rejected. The frustration came in the understanding that it wasn’t a rejection born of time constraints, or budget, or even ignorance..&quot;<br>
<br>
You can find the whole post, regarding his announcement and reasons <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=50044235&amp;replies=79" target="top">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
Shortly after, the new Armsman Teamleader was chosen. Galahad_Mors, who plays an Armsman on the Galahad Server, was selected to represent the Armsman class. I searched for a post regarding this, however, I was only able to find this..<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=50705393&amp;replies=55" target="top">First TL Report in the DAoC TL Reports Section</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
I can't say that i'v met or seen this person, but from what I have read, he seems very deticated to his class and makes sure that they are heard and recieve the attention that they need.<br>
<br>
Mors is currently putting up a site deticated to the Armsman. The site is still under construction, but he has an up and running board. You can find the board <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.meatshield.com/boards/ubbthreads.php" target="top">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
I would like to bring your attention to Shirfs post regarding his dismissal..<br>
<br>
&quot;I see the TL program moving in a direction that doesn’t need me. I believe that upcoming changes move the program away from a players testing and reporting situation and more into a “are enough people playing X class, or Y spec, or paying for Z ability” arena. They don’t need or really seem to want player feedback in this area via the TLs; they have all of the data in-hand and have experienced people taking over decision-making positions. Soon TLs will not even report bugs in the TL reports. Instead, TLs will express the less concrete, such as “How well does the class functions in solo PvE?” or “Does the class have the tools it needs to fill its role in RvR?” While this will be player-feedback oriented, anyone with a firm understanding of the game and the ability to write well could probably do an excellent write-up for half of the classed in his or her chosen realm. I’m not that eloquent.&quot;<br>
<br>
If what Shirf sais is true (And I believe him), then there is no longer a need to record our daily beatings. It doesn't matter how bad we are out on the field, aslong as we are getting enough people creating/playing the class, then we're &quot;fixed&quot;. I find this appauling, and very dissheartening. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
k8t, it would make me feel a lot better if I could get your view on this. I don't want to see your work go to waste, nor do I want us to be ignored. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I do, however, wish Mors the best of luck. I don't know how things are going to turn out, and that lack of knowledge frightens me.  <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
